@NODE INSTA "Installation"

@{b}REQUIREMENTS@{ub}

- AGA chipset, hard disk, 2 Mb of Chip-Ram free
- Memory expansion or accelerator is highly reccomended to avoid slowdowns
- A joystick with 2 fire buttons is also reccomended for better playability

@{b}INSTALLING AND STARTING THE GAME@{ub}

1. Boot your Workbench as usual
2. Insert the original Gunbee F-99 Disk 1
3. Run the "HD_Install" program and follow its indications
4. After the installation process has finished, remove the original disks, go
   to the path where the game was installed and double-click the "Gunbee_F99".
5. You'll see the F-99 Early Configuration screen. Read the instructions, set
   the options and then press fire to start the intro.

@{b}VIDEO TIPS@{ub}

If your display device supports NTSC video signal, you could try to select it
in the F-99 Early Config to get a bigger screen view.

If your computer hasn't an accelerator card and your display device supports
PAL signal, then select it to avoid possible slowdowns.

@{b}PROBLEMS...@{ub}
     
If the game doesn't run, reset your computer to clean up memory and retry.
If it fails again, you should access the "Amiga Early Startup Control" screen
(reset and hold down both mouse buttons) and Boot Without StartUp Sequence.
Now, directly from the Shell, run Gunbee F-99.

Make sure you have installed the original "mathtrans.library" file (supplied
with your Workbench 3.x installation disks) otherwise the game will crash.

@ENDNODE
 

@NODE SHORT "Introduction"

@{b}THE STORY...@{ub}

For many years, Valstyx was a peaceful planet in the Universe. Five Magic
Crystals owned by Lady Akiko, the princess of Valstyx, guaranteed the power
and stability of the whole planet.

But one day things changed. Strange beasts and bizarre machines suddenly
invaded the planet. It was being taken over by Lord Khenmir's evil forces.

In a surprisedly attack, the Soldiers were unable to defend the Royal Palace.
And while the chaos involved the kingdom, Lord Khenmir took possession of the
Five Magic Crystals... and kidnapped princess Akiko.

Designed with the very best of Valstyx technology, you, as Kiara McGuire, will
pilot the GUNBEE F-99, a mobile suit developed by the Royal Engineers with the
hope to defeat Lord Khenmir big guardians, to recover the Five Magic Crystals
and succeed in the save of the beautiful Lady Akiko.

Good luck!

@ENDNODE


@NODE PLAYN "Playing Gunbee F-99"

@{b}01.- THE CONTROLS@{ub}

You control Gunbee F-99 with the joystick in port 2:

Move toward any direction to fly.
Press Fire 1 quickly to shoot.
Press Fire 1 longer to shoot a Firebeam.
Press Fire 2 to throw a bomb.

The 'space key' can be used as 2nd. fire button.

Alternatively you can use the Keyboard:

Cursors Keys to fly.
Left AMIGA quickly to shoot.
Left AMIGA longer to launch a Firebeam.
Left ALT to throw a bomb.

In-Game Keys:

Press "P" to pause the game, again to resume.
Press "ESC" to exit current game and return to menu.


@{b}02.- GUNBEE F-99 WEAPONS@{ub}

THE STANDARD WEAPONS

There are three standard weapons: you begin with the slowest SingleShot.
Standard weapons are upgradeable by collecting more Power-Up Bells.

THE FIREBEAM

A powerful flame effective to quickly open your way. Hold fire button longer
to accumulate enough energy, then release it. The higher you accumulate, the
more powerful the Firebeam will be.

THE BOMB

The only weapon capable of destroying enemy ground bases. Press 2nd. fire
button to throw a bomb. Some practice is needed to lock them.
  
THE MACHINE-GUN

A powerful weapon available for Gunbee F-99P Planetary Type but with limited
ammo rounds. Extra ammo clips can be found hidden below some clouds.


@{b}03.- THE BELLS@{ub}

Bells are one of the most important items in the game. These are hidden below
some Smiling Clouds. Shoot the clouds to release gold bells, and shoot quickly
the bells to change its colour.

To get the bells just fly over it:

Gold Bell  - Points   : 500 points.
Blue Bell  - Speed Up : improves Gunbee flight speed.
Green Bell - Power Up : improves Gunbee fire power, then switch next weapon.
White Bell - Shield   : Gunbee Shield aprox. 20 seconds (limited availability).
Red Bell   - Firebeam : supply an extra Firebeam.
Black Bell - Damage   : these must be avoided as Gunbee will lose its arms
                           (and ability to throw bombs).


@{b}04.- THE FLYING AMBULANCE@{ub}

When Gunbee F-99 is damaged a Flying Ambulance will appear in the sky. Fly over
it to dock and be healed. When undocking a Shield will protect you while you
fly to a safe location. In case you lose the ambulance, you may have another
chance if you put any Bell into the Flying Basket from a high altitude.
               

@{b}05.- THE FLYING BASKET@{ub}

The Flying Basket is released when an entire enemy wave was shootdown while
some Smiling Clouds are yet flying in the sky. The colorful winged Basket does
the job of a Bell Collector.

Another use of the bells is to make land them into the Basket by knocking them
around the screen with accurate and well timed shoots. Each time you collect
10 Bells of whatever color in the Basket you'll get an Extra-Live.

Check for other objects that may be also put into the Flying Basket.


@{b}06.- THE KITTY-KATRANSPORT CLOUD@{ub}

Occasionally you will hear suddenly an alert sound. This signals that a
Kitty-Katransport Cloud (KTC) is just flying in the zone. The KTC looks
like a 'cat face' and always carries important items. Shoot to this special
cloud to release the hidden item.


@{b}07.- THE KITTY-KATRANSPORT ITEMS@{ub}

THE HIGH FIREBEAM

This KTC item looks like a 'blue box with a red flame in middle' and will
improve your Firebeam weapon allowing to shoot a bigger flame. To get this
upgrade just fly over the item.

THE MAGIC CRYSTALS

Akiko's Crystals are the most important items in the game. They looks of
different colour according to the level: blue, red, yellow, green and white.
                                
To recover a Magic Crystal you must put it into the Flying Basket by knocking
it around the screen with accurate shoots. Read carefully the "Flying Basket"
section to understand how the Basket is released. Some practice and strategy
is needed to succeed.
 
THE GB01/P KIT (GUNBEE F-99P PLANETARY TYPE)

This KTC item looks like a 'dark brown box with white exclamation in middle'.
Royal Engineers developed the GB01/P Kit to upgrade your Gunbee F-99 into the
F-99P Planetary. This type provides two hand-held Machine-Gun weapon as also
stabilizers to eliminate the turbulence at very high altitudes.

Shoot quickly the brown box to make it explode, then a wellow pack will be
released. To get the GB/01P upgrade kit just fly over the released item.
Gunbee F-99P Planetary will activate when entering the next world.

THE MACHINE-GUN AMMO CLIPS

When flying the F-99P Planetary Type, the weapon with most priority is the
Machine-Gun. Unfortunately, Royal Engineers were unable to provide extra ammo
carriage so you have a limited machine-gun rounds to shoot.

Extra ammo clips will be supplied through Kitty-Katransport Clouds. To reload
the Machine-Gun, just fly over the item.


@{b}08.- GROUND ATTACK@{ub}
                                                             
Enemy bases looks quiet but sometimes are very dangerous. It is easy to be
trapped by their shoots or suddenly to be damaged just when flying over them.
The only way to prevent ground attack is throwing a Bomb to destroy bases.

Destroyed enemy bases will release a ground Bonus. Fly over it to get it.


@{b}09.- THE PLAYER WINDOW STATUS@{Ub}

"Heart", player's available lives (maximum allowed is 5)
"Flying Basket", bells collected into the baskets.
"Firebeams", Firebeams available.
"MG Rounds", MachineGun rounds available.
"Crystals", Magic Crystals recovered.

The "Firebeam Bar" shows the power accumulation when holding the fire button.

@{b}10.- THE HIGH SCORE TABLE@{Ub}

POS..... position rank
SCORE... points
NAME.... name of the player
BELLS... total bells collected in the Flying Basket
WAVE.... total enemy waves destroyed
END..... Happy Smile...... Lady Akiko was saved
         Sad Smile........ Lady Akiko was not saved
         Skull............ player died
         Letter at left... "H"=Honey Mode, "S"=Story Mode
         Number at right.. Level reached.

Note: High-Scores are saved when you QUIT the game.

@ENDNODE


@NODE OPTIO "Options Screen"

@{b}THE OPTIONS SCREEN@{ub}

@{b}1.- GAME MODES@{ub}

Press fire button to switch between Honey or Story mode.

@{b}Story Mode@{ub}

All the rules explained in the manual apply to this mode. The main objective
of this mode is to successfully rescue lovely princess Akiko by recovering all
the Five Magic Crystals. The word 'ability' is the main key to survive in this
mode because you will have to pay special attention to:

- collect 10 Bells into the Flying Baskets to gain more lives
- recover the Magic Crystals
- collect Kitty-Katransport Clouds items (High Firebeam, GB01/P Kit, etc.)
- avoid more enemy shots and boss attack initiatives.

@{b}Honey Mode@{ub}

Almost all the rules explained in this manual applies to this mode with the
following exceptions:

- you begin with 5 Lives and 5 Firebeams
- Kitty-Katransport Clouds not available
- Magic Crystals not available
- KTC items not available (no GB01/P kit, MG AmmoClip and High Firebeam)
- Gunbee F99P Planetary mode not available
- turbulence not available
- High Firebeam always available
- Extra-lives every 100,000 points
- No Extra-lives when 10 Bells are collected into Flying Basket
- Less enemy attack initiative
- Enemy weird shots not available
- Big Guardians shoots slow and less attack modes.

In this mode you can learn the rules of the game, to plan some strategy and to
practice useful tactics for hard situations in the levels. Surviving is easy
because you're provided with more initial lives and a faster way to get extra
lives. The no need to pay attention to KTC items (like the Crystals) and other
rules (like knocking bells into the Baskets) means you can safely fly in
the sky without worrying about all that.

Honey Mode also provides a Level Selection, for training purpose.

@{b}2.- MUSIC@{ub}

Press to switch On/Off the in-game music. Sound effects will be played alone.

@{b}3.- INTRO@{ub}

Show again the game introduction.

@{b}4.- LEVEL SELECTION@{ub}
                           
Option available only in Honey Mode. Move the joystick left or right to choose
the level and fire to begin. A level is selectable only if the player has
reached it in the current game session, being level 4 the last one allowed.
Previous score and performance is not keept.

@ENDNODE


@NODE TIPS "Tips & Tricks"

@{b}GUNBEE F99 TIPS@{ub}

- When a level begins, collect inmediatelly useful bells (green and blue)
  to improve your flight performance. The more powerful is the Gunbee F99,
  the less performance is lost if you die.

- Be careful when flying below the Clouds. Slow enemy shots may be there.

- If you die search inmediatelly a Green Bell to try to get back your
  previous shooting rate. Also pay attention for any extra Firebeam supplied.

- Remember that the Flying Basket is released when you shootdown an enemy
  wave while some Smiling Clouds are flying in the sky.

- If your shooting rate is slow, then don't shoot quickly. Use paused and
  accurate shoots while you power-up.

- Don't wast Firebeams. They are very useful in special situations like to
  quickly shootdown an enemy wave or just make your way if you feel trapped.

- Don't wast White Bell. Shields are limited for each level. If a white bell
  appears and you don't need it, then don't get it! In this way the Shield
  may appear later in the level.

- Destroyed ground enemy bases may give an Lives bonus. Extra Lives can be
  obtained by collecting 10 Bells into Flying Basket (Story mode) or every
  100,000 points (Honey Mode).

@ENDNODE


